3.SOLUTION OF PARSER:
		 A parser creates a parse tree for a sentences in which each word is defined as an object. Each object represents some additional information about each word that includes Parts Of Speech(POS), word ID, parse ID, A parse tree represents the root word for every sentence, and the relationship among every word to one another prrsent in the sentence. This makes it easier for the tool to form a sentence depending on the construct of each woed or chunk of words. 
		 
		 EX.English Sentence: The Indus and its tributaries – the Jhelum, the Chenab, the Ravi,the Beas and the Satluj originate in the Himalaya.
  		    Hindi Sentence  :सिंधु तथा इसकी सहायक नदियाँ झेलम , चेनाब , रावी , ब्यास तथा सतलुज हिमालय से निकलती हैं .(Ex. reffer this sentence from 			    Geo_chap2_E2 sentence no.2.99)
   		 
		 =>Solution of Parser-Run parser again by changing  the POS of originate to VERB as originate is never occured as NOUN. 

